Soul musician and Grammy-award winner Seal and his son, Henry were over the weekend hosted to a dinner by oil magnate Femi Otedola in his house in Lagos. Posting pictures on his Instagram the billionaire made the revelation. “Pleasure having world-renowned singer @Seal and his son Henry over for dinner at our home yesterday evening,” Otedola wrote. In the picture, DJ Cuppy, Otedola, Seal and his son, Henry are seen at the dinner table. Last week, pictures of the British born singer of Nigerian origin and his son when they visited Femi Kuti at the New Afrika Shrine, Ikeja, Lagos first surfaced when Femi Kuti tweeted it. Known professionally as Seal, he was born Henry Olusegun Adeola Samuel in Paddington, London on Februrary 19, 1963. He has sold over 20 million records worldwide and he is very popular for his song, ‘Kiss from a Rose’, released in 1994. Seal has won many awards, including three Brit Awards, four Grammy Awards and an MTV Video Music Award. He also received two Ivor Novello Awards for Best Song Musically and Lyrically from the British Academy of Songwriters, Composers, and Authors for ‘Killer’ (1990) and ‘Crazy’ (1991). He was a coach on The Voice Australia in 2012 and 2013 and returned to Australia to work as a coach in 2017. He was married to Heidi Klum between 2005 and 2014.